<eesti>I peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter I </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomand </eesti>
<inglise>Apartment Ownership </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of apartment ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomand on omand ehitise reaalosaks olevale korterile ning reaalosa suurusele vastavale m&otilde;ttelisele osale nii maat&uuml;kist kui selle oluliseks osaks oleva ehitise osast, mis ei ole &uuml;hegi korteriomandi reaalosa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Apartment ownership is ownership of an apartment which is a physical share of a structure, and of a legal share corresponding to the size of the physical share of both the plot of land and the essential part of the structure which is not a physical share of any apartment ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korteriomand loetakse kinnisasjaks ning sellele kohaldatakse asja&otilde;igusseaduse (RT I 1993, 39, 590; 1999, 44, 509) kinnisomandi s&auml;tteid, kui k&auml;esolevas seaduses ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Apartment ownerships shall be deemed to be immovables and the immovable property ownership provisions of the Law of Property Act (RT I 1993, 39, 590; 1999, 44, 509) apply thereto unless otherwise provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi ese </eesti>
<inglise>Object of apartment ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomandi ese on ehituslikult tegelikkuses piiritletud omaette kasutust v&otilde;imaldav eluruum, samuti selle ruumi juurde kuuluvad ehitise osad koos eluruumi &uuml;ldpinna suurusele vastava reaalosaks mitteoleva ehitiseosa ja maat&uuml;ki m&otilde;ttelise osaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The object of apartment ownership is a residential space which is delimited in real terms by construction and enables independent use, and the parts of the structure belonging to the space together with a legal share of the part of the structure which is not a physical share and of the plot of land which correspond to the total area of the residential space. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses v&otilde;ib korteriomandi eseme reaalosaks olla ka mitteeluruum. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, the physical share of an object of apartment ownership may also be a non-residential space. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eluruumi piires on reaalosaks ehitise osad, mida v&otilde;ib muuta v&otilde;i eemaldada, ilma et kahjustataks m&otilde;ttelisi osi, teiste korteriomanike &otilde;igusi ning muudetakse hoone v&auml;list kuju. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Within the boundaries of a residential space, a physical share is the part of the structure which may be altered or removed without damaging the legal shares or the rights of other apartment owners, or altering the external form of the building. </inglise>
<eesti>Reaalosaks ei ole ehitise osad, samuti rajatised ja seadmed, mis on vajalikud ehitise p&uuml;simiseks, ohutuse tagamiseks v&otilde;i korteriomanike &uuml;hiseks kasutamiseks, ka siis, kui need asuvad eluruumi piires. </eesti>
<inglise>The parts of a structure or the constructions and equipment which are necessary for the life of the structure, for ensuring safety or for common use of the apartment owners are not physical shares even if such parts are situated within the boundaries of a residential space. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korteriomandi esemeks olevat ehitise reaalosa ning sellele vastavat reaalosaks mitteolevat ehitiseosa ja maat&uuml;ki m&otilde;ttelist osa ei saa teineteisest eraldi v&otilde;&otilde;randada, koormata ega p&auml;randada. (4) Korteriomand ei v&otilde;i ulatuda teisele maat&uuml;kile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The physical share of a structure which is an object of apartment ownership, and the corresponding legal share of the part of the structure which is not a physical share and of the plot of land cannot be transferred, encumbered or bequeathed separately (4) Apartment ownership shall not extend to another plot of land. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomanik </eesti>
<inglise>Apartment owner </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi omanik (edaspidi korteriomanik) v&otilde;ib olla riik, kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus, f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, era&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik ja seaduses s&auml;testatud omanikuks olev avalik-&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner of an apartment ownership (hereinafter apartment owner) may be the state, a local government, a natural person, a legal person in private law or a legal person in public law who is the owner provided by its Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnisomandi jagamine korteriomanditeks </eesti>
<inglise>Division of immovable property ownership into apartment ownerships </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomanditeks v&otilde;ib jagada kinnisomandi, mille esemeks on maat&uuml;kk &uuml;hes sellel oleva v&otilde;i ehitatava ehitisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Immovable property ownership the object of which is a plot of land together with a structure or a structure to be built thereon may be divided into apartment ownerships. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korteriomanditeks v&otilde;ib jagada kinnisomandit &uuml;ksnes tervikuna. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Immovable property ownership may be divided into apartment ownerships only in its entirety. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kinnisomandi jagamisel korteriomanditeks v&otilde;ib ehitise m&otilde;ne eluruumi v&otilde;i mitteeluruumi j&auml;tta korteriomandite eseme m&otilde;ttelisteks osadeks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon division of immovable property ownership into apartment ownerships, some residential or non-residential spaces of the structure may remain as legal shares of the objects of apartment ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi tekkimine juurdeehitamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Creation of apartment ownership upon building addition to structure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomanditeks jaotatud kinnisasjale seaduslikult juurde ehitatud osale tekib korteriomand vastava kinnistusraamatu kande tegemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Apartment ownership of a legally built addition to an immovables which is divided into apartment ownerships is created by making a corresponding land registry entry. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korteriomanditeks jaotatud kinnisasjale v&otilde;ib teha juurdeehituse, mis v&otilde;ib olla uute korteriomandite tekkimise aluseks k&otilde;igi seniste korteriomandite omanike kokkuleppe alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An addition may be built to an immovable divided into apartment ownerships on the basis of which new apartment ownerships may be created based on the agreement of all current owners of apartment ownerships. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkuleppes n&auml;idatakse seniste korteriomanike m&otilde;tteliste osade suuruse muutus, uue korteriomandi reaalosa ja selle juurde kuuluva m&otilde;ttelise osa suurus ning kellele v&otilde;&otilde;randatakse juurdeehitatav korteriomand ning keda volitatakse tegema juurdeehitusega seotud vajalikke toiminguid. </eesti>
<inglise>The agreement shall set out the size of the legal shares of the current owners, the physical share of the new apartment ownership and the size of legal share belonging thereto, the person to whom the addition to be built is transferred, and the person authorised to perform necessary acts related to the building of the addition. </inglise>
<eesti>Allkirjad kokkuleppel peavad olema notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud. </eesti>
<inglise>The signatures in the agreement shall be notarised. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juurdeehitus teostatakse planeerimis- ja ehitusseaduses ning muudes kehtivates &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Additions shall be built pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Planning and Building Act and other legislation in force. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kande tegemise aluseks on seniste korteriomanike ja juurdeehitatud korteriomandi omandaja v&otilde;i nende esindajate notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud kinnistamisavaldus, milles n&auml;idatakse &auml;ra seniste korteriomandite m&otilde;tteliste osade muutmise ulatus ja uue korteriomandi kohta k&auml;ivad andmed vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 6 l&otilde;ikele 2. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The basis for the entry is a notarised registration application of the current apartment owners and the purchaser of the apartment ownership of the built addition or their representatives which shall set out the extent of change in the legal shares in the current apartment ownerships and information concerning the new apartment ownership pursuant to subsection 6 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Koos uue korteriomandi registrisse kandmisega tehakse vajalikud muudatused seniste korteriomandite kannetes. </eesti>
<inglise>Necessary amendments to the entries of current apartment ownerships are made together with the entry in the register of the new apartment ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.06.98 j&otilde;ust.10.07.98 - RT I 1998, 59, 941) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.06.98 entered into force 10.07.98 - RT I 1998, 59, 941) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi tekkimine </eesti>
<inglise>Creation of apartment ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomand tekib kinnistusraamatusse kandmisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Apartment ownership is created by entry in the land register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Omanik v&otilde;ib kinnisomandi jagada korteriomanditeks notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud &uuml;hepoolse kinnistamisavalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An owner may divide immovable property ownership into apartment ownerships on the basis of a notarised unilateral registration application. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaasomandis oleva kinnisomandi v&otilde;ib jagada korteriomanditeks k&otilde;igi kaasomanike &uuml;hise notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud kinnistamisavalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Immovable property ownership in common ownership may be divided into apartment ownerships on the basis of a joint notarised registration application by all the co-owners. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korteriomand on &uuml;hendatav ja jagatav asja&otilde;igusseaduse paragrahv 54 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Apartment ownership may be merged and divided on the basis of &sect; 54 of the Law of Property Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnistamisavaldusele peab olema lisatud vastav projekt. </eesti>
<inglise>A corresponding design shall be appended to the registration application. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.97 j&otilde;ust.03.01.98 - RT I 1997, 93, 1566) </eesti>
<inglise>(9.12.97 entered into force 3 01.98 - RT I 1997, 93, 1566) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi kinnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of apartment ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Igale korteriomandile avatakse &uuml;heaegselt kinnistusregistri iseseisev osa ja kinnisasja senine registriosa suletakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An independent land register part is opened concurrently for each apartment ownership and the current register part for the immovable is closed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avatava kinnistusregistri osa vastavatesse jagudesse kantakse &uuml;le suletud registriosa andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information from the closed register part is transferred to the corresponding divisions of the land register part being opened. </inglise>
<eesti>Registriosa esimesse jakku kantakse ka korteri number, &uuml;ldpinna suurus, m&otilde;ttelise osa suurus, teiste korteriomandite registriosade numbrid. </eesti>
<inglise>The apartment number, total area, size of the legal share and the numbers of the other apartment ownership register parts are also entered in the first division of the register part. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise jakku kantakse korteriomaniku nimi. </eesti>
<inglise>The name of the apartment owner is entered in the second division. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui korteriomand on &uuml;hine omand, m&auml;rgitakse &uuml;histe omanike nimed, kaasomandi korral ka osade suurused. </eesti>
<inglise>If the apartment ownership is in shared ownership, the names of the joint owners and, in the case of common ownership, also the size of the shares are noted. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korteriomandi registriosa avamiseks tuleb esitada kinnistamisavaldus, Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;ratud asutuse poolt v&auml;lja antud dokument (plaan) ehitise, eluruumide ja mitteeluruumide, reaalosade ja m&otilde;tteliste osade suuruse ja paiknemise kohta ja muud seadusest tulenevad kinnistamiseks vajalikud dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to open an apartment ownership register part, a registration application, the document (plan) issued by the agency designated by the Government of the Republic concerning the size and location of the structure, the residential and non-residential spaces, the physical and legal shares, and other documents necessary for registration pursuant to law shall be submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi eseme reaalosaks olevad ruumid t&auml;histatakse plaanil &uuml;he ja sama korterinumbriga. </eesti>
<inglise>Spaces which are physical shares of an object of apartment ownership are denoted on the plan by the same apartment number. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of apartment ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomand l&otilde;peb kande kustutamisega kinnistusraamatust, samuti korteriomandite registriosade sulgemisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Apartment ownership terminates by deletion of the entry from the land register or by closure of apartment ownership register parts. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korteriomandite registriosad v&otilde;ib sulgeda &uuml;heaegselt j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Apartment ownership register parts may be closed concurrently in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&otilde;igi korteriomanike notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud kinnistamisavalduse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on the basis of a notarised registration application by all the apartment owners; </inglise>
<eesti>2) korteriomanike enamuse notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud kinnistamisavalduse alusel, kui ehitis on t&auml;ielikult h&auml;vinud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) on the basis of a notarised registration application by a majority of the apartment owners if the structure is completely destroyed; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isiku notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud avalduse alusel, kui ta on omandanud k&otilde;ik korteriomandid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) on the basis of a notarised application by a person if the person has acquired all the apartment ownerships. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korteriomandi registriosade sulgemisel avatakse kinnisasja kohta registriosa asja&otilde;igusseaduses ja kinnistusraamatuseaduses (RT I 1993, 65, 922; 1999, 44, 511) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon closure of apartment ownership register parts, a register part is opened concerning the immovable pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Law of Property Act and the Land Register Act (RT I 1993, 65, 922; 1999, 44, 511). </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike punktides 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud alustel j&auml;&auml;b kinnisasi endiste korteriomanike kaasomandisse, kusjuures iga&uuml;he kaasomandiosa suurus vastab neile kuulunud m&otilde;ttelise osa suurusele, kui k&otilde;igi korteriomanike kokkuleppel ei m&auml;&auml;ratud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>On the basis provided for in clauses (2) 1) and 2) of this section, the immovable remains in the common ownership of the previous apartment owners and the size of the share of common ownership of each owner shall correspond to the size of the legal share which belonged to them unless otherwise specified by agreement of all the apartment owners. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui korteriomandite registriosade sulgemine puudutab kolmandate isikute &otilde;igusi, ei v&otilde;i korteriomandite registriosasid sulgeda nende isikute n&otilde;usolekuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If closure of the apartment ownership register parts affects the rights of third persons, the apartment ownership register parts shall not be closed without the consent of the third persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Korteriomandi registriosade sulgemisel l&otilde;pevad korteriomandile seatud asja&otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon closure of the apartment ownership register parts, the real rights established in the apartment ownership terminate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi k&auml;sutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disposal of apartment ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomanikul on &otilde;igus korteriomandit v&otilde;&otilde;randada, p&auml;randada, anda teiste isikute kasutusse, samuti koormata servituudi, reaalkoormatise, ostuees&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i kinnispandiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An apartment owner has the right to transfer, bequeath or grant use of an apartment ownership to other persons or to encumber it with a servitude, real encumbrance, right of pre-emption or real security. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teisel korteriomanikul on korteriomandi ostuees&otilde;igus ainult siis, kui see on tema kasuks seatud tehingu v&otilde;i seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Another apartment owner has the right of pre-emption of an apartment ownership only if this is established for the benefit of the apartment owner by a transaction or law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korteriomanikul ei ole &otilde;igust n&otilde;uda temale kuuluva maat&uuml;ki ja ehitise m&otilde;ttelise osa eraldamist reaalosana. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An apartment owner does not have the right to demand severance as a physical share of a legal share of a structure or a plot of land belonging to the apartment owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korteriomandi v&otilde;&otilde;randamisel v&otilde;i p&auml;rimisel l&auml;hevad korteriomandi v&otilde;&otilde;randajale v&otilde;i p&auml;randajale kuuluvad korteri&uuml;histu liikme &otilde;igused ja kohustused &uuml;le korteriomandi omandajale korteriomandi &uuml;lemineku hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon transfer or succession of an apartment ownership, the rights and obligations of an apartment association member which belong to the transferor or bequeather of the apartment ownership transfer to the acquirer of the apartment ownership at the time of transfer of the apartment ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi valdamine ja kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Possession and use of apartment ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomanikul on &otilde;igus m&otilde;ttelisi osi kasutada vastavalt nende otstarbele niiv&otilde;rd, kui see ei takista teiste korteriomanike kaaskasutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An apartment owner has the right to use the legal shares according to their purpose in so far as this does not hinder co-use by the other apartment owners. </inglise>
<eesti>Sama kehtib korteriomaniku perekonnaliikmete, ajutiste elanike ja isikute kohta, kes kasutavad reaalosa lepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The same applies to family members of the apartment owner, temporary residents and persons who use the physical share on the basis of an agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korteriomanikul on &otilde;igus teha m&otilde;tteliste osade s&auml;ilitamiseks vajalikke toiminguid teiste korteriomanike n&otilde;usolekuta, kuid ta v&otilde;ib teistelt korteriomanikelt n&otilde;uda vajalike kulutuste h&uuml;vitamist v&otilde;rdeliselt nende m&otilde;tteliste osade suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An apartment owner has the right to perform acts necessary for preservation of the legal shares without the consent of the other apartment owners, and the apartment owner may demand reimbursement of necessary expenses from the other apartment owners in proportion to the size of their legal shares. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korteriomanikul on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda teistelt korteriomanikelt, et m&otilde;tteliste osade valdamine ja kasutamine toimuks vastavalt k&otilde;igi korteriomanike huvidele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An apartment owner has the right to demand that the other apartment owners possess and use the legal shares according to the interests of all apartment owners. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korteriomanik peab lubama reaalosa kasutamist teiste isikute poolt, kui see on vajalik korteriomandi esemeks olevate m&otilde;tteliste osade korrashoiuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An apartment owner shall permit the use of a physical share by other persons if this is necessary for maintenance of the legal shares of the object of apartment ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hine tegutsemine </eesti>
<inglise>Joint activity </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomanikud tegutsevad m&otilde;tteliste osade majandamisel &uuml;hiselt ja reaalosade puhul iseseisvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Apartment owners shall act jointly in the management of the legal shares and independently with regard to the physical shares. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korteriomandite m&otilde;tteliste osade majandamiseks asutatakse korteri&uuml;histu, mille liikmeks on iga korteriomanik v&otilde;i s&otilde;lmitakse &uuml;hise tegutsemise leping k&otilde;igi korteriomanike vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An apartment association of which each apartment owner is a member shall be founded for management of the legal shares of the apartment ownerships, or a contract for joint activity shall be entered into by all the apartment owners. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduses v&otilde;ib s&auml;testada juhud, millal korteri&uuml;histu asutamine on kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>Cases in which foundation of an apartment association is obligatory may be provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) M&otilde;tteliste osade majandamise kulutused kannavad korteriomanikud v&otilde;rdeliselt neile kuuluvate m&otilde;tteliste osade suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Apartment owners shall bear the management expenses of the legal shares in proportion to the size of the legal shares belonging to them. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomanik ei vastuta kulutuste eest, mis &uuml;letavad m&otilde;tteliste osade korrap&auml;rase korrashoiu ning remondi vajadused ja millega ta ei ole n&otilde;ustunud. </eesti>
<inglise>An apartment owner is not liable for expenses which exceed the regular maintenance and repair requirements of the legal shares and to which the apartment owner has not consented. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomanike otsused </eesti>
<inglise>Resolutions of apartment owners </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Otsused m&otilde;tteliste osade majandamiseks tehakse korteriomanike h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega, kui korteri&uuml;histu p&otilde;hikirjast ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Resolutions for management of legal shares shall be made by a majority vote of the apartment owners unless otherwise provided by the articles of association of the apartment association. </inglise>
<eesti>Iga korteriomand annab &uuml;he h&auml;&auml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>Each apartment ownership has one vote. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui korteriomand on &uuml;hine omand, teostavad &uuml;hised omanikud h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igust &uuml;hiselt. </eesti>
<inglise>If an apartment ownership is in shared ownership, the joint owners shall exercise the right to vote jointly. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud otsus m&otilde;tteliste osade majandamiseks kehtib iga ja igakordse korteriomaniku suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The resolution specified in subsection (1) of this section for management of legal shares is valid with respect to each and to each subsequent apartment owner. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus ei v&otilde;i kitsendada korteriomandi k&auml;sutamist ega kolmandate isikute &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise>A resolution shall not restrict disposal of an apartment ownership or the rights of third persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksud, koormatised ja viljad </eesti>
<inglise>Taxation, encumbrances and fruits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korteriomanikud tasuvad k&otilde;ik m&otilde;ttelistel osadel lasuvad maksud ja kannavad avalik-&otilde;iguslikud reaalkoormatised v&otilde;rdeliselt neile kuuluvate m&otilde;tteliste osade suurusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Apartment owners shall pay all taxes incumbent on the legal shares and bear real encumbrances in public law in proportion to the size of the legal shares belonging to them. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Igale korteriomanikule kuulub tema m&otilde;ttelise osa suurusele vastav osa m&otilde;tteliste osade viljast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A part of the fruit of the legal shares corresponding to the size of an apartment owner's share belongs to the apartment owner. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Korterihoonestus&otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right of superficies in apartments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Hoonestaja v&otilde;ib jagada talle kuuluva hoonestus&otilde;iguse korterihoonestus&otilde;igusteks maat&uuml;ki omaniku n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A superficiary may divide a right of superficies belonging to the superficiary into a right of superficies in apartments with the consent of the owner of the plot of land. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maat&uuml;kk ei v&otilde;i samaaegselt olla korteriomandi esemeks ja koormatud korterihoonestus&otilde;igusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A plot of land shall not concurrently be an object of apartment ownership and be encumbered with a right of superficies in apartments. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korterihoonestus&otilde;iguse esemeks on ehituslikult tegelikkuses piiritletud omaette kasutust v&otilde;imaldav eluruum v&otilde;i mitteeluruum, samuti selle juurde kuuluvad ehitise osad, koos selle &uuml;ldpinna suurusele vastava m&otilde;ttelise osaga reaalosaks mitteolevast ehitise osast ja hoonestus&otilde;igusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The object of a right of superficies in apartments is a residential or non-residential space which is delimited in real terms by construction and enables independent use, and the parts of the structure belonging thereto together with a legal share of the part of the structure which is not a physical share corresponding to its total area and of the right of superficies. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Igale korterihoonestus&otilde;igusele avatakse &uuml;heaegselt kinnistusregistri iseseisev osa ja hoonestus&otilde;iguse senine registriosa suletakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An independent land register part is opened concurrently for each right of superficies in apartments and the current right of superficies in apartments register part is closed. </inglise>
<eesti>Koormatud kinnisasja registriossa tehakse kanne hoonestus&otilde;iguse jagamise kohta korterihoonestus&otilde;igusteks. </eesti>
<inglise>An entry concerning division of a right of superficies into rights of superficies in apartments is made in the register part for the encumbered immovable. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Korterihoonestus&otilde;igusele kohaldatakse muus osas korteriomandit ja hoonestus&otilde;igust reguleerivaid s&auml;tteid, kui seaduses ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The provisions regulating apartment ownership and right of superficies apply to other aspects of a right of superficies in apartments unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>Korteriomandi esemeks oleva maat&uuml;ki m&otilde;ttelise osa kohta k&auml;ivad s&auml;tted kehtivad korteri hoonestus&otilde;iguse esemeks oleva hoonestus&otilde;iguse m&otilde;ttelise osa suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions concerning the legal share of a plot of land which is an object of apartment ownership are valid with respect to a legal share of a right of superficies which is the object of a right of superficies in apartments. </inglise>
